    <h1>About the Brewer</h1>
    <p>Doug “Old Man” Walker brewed his first all-grain batch on July 31, 2021 using a Grainfather G40. What started as a curiosity quickly turned into a garage project, then into a garage brewery — complete with a dedicated sink, PEX plumbing, a chiller, a sparge tank, and over 300 pounds of grain in rotation.</p>

    <p>He brews under the name <strong>Rusty Nut Brew ’n Que</strong>, a nod to the busted knuckles and late-night sessions that take place in the third bay of his garage.</p>

    <h2>Brewing Timeline</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>First batch: July 31, 2021</li>
      <li>50th batch: September 18, 2022</li>
      <li>100th batch: August 20, 2023</li>
      <li>Became a certified BJCP Judge: March 2024</li>
      <li>Authored a BJCP Tasting Exam Study Guide: March 2024</li>
      <li>Achieved Master Rank from MHP: 2024</li>
      <li>150th batch: September 24, 2024</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Competitions</h2>
    <p>Doug entered his first competition in late 2022. Since then, he’s brewed across more than 40 styles and submitted beers to competitions throughout California and beyond. He tracks every result—wins, near misses, and performance by style—and posts the raw data.</p>

    <p>Selected milestones:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>First Best of Show (3rd) – 2023 Brix Oktoberfest</li>
      <li>First Best of Show (1st) – 2024 California Homebrew Competition</li>
      <li>Silver Medal – 2024 National Homebrew Competition Finals</li>
      <li>Heavy Medal Brewer – 2025 Pacific Brewers Cup</li>
    </ul>

